        <!-- UK Market Context 2026 -->
        <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-indigo-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-indigo-400 pl-4">UK Web Development Market in 2026</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">The UK web development market has shifted significantly in recent years. Several trends affect what you'll pay and what you'll get:</p>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
            <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">AI Is Reducing Build Time</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Developers using AI coding tools (Copilot, Kiro, Cursor) can deliver the same quality in less time. Forward-thinking studios pass these savings to clients through faster delivery, not inflated margins.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
            <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Serverless Has Killed Hosting Costs</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Platforms like Cloudflare Workers, Vercel, and Netlify offer generous free tiers. A site that cost £100/month to host in 2020 can now run for free — with better performance.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
            <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">WordPress Costs Are Rising</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Plugin licensing fees, security overhead, and hosting requirements for WordPress have increased. Many businesses are migrating to static-first frameworks for lower total cost of ownership.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
            <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">SEO Is Non-Negotiable</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Google's AI overviews and featured snippets mean a website without SEO strategy is invisible. Structured data, Core Web Vitals, and content depth are table stakes in 2026.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">The net effect: build costs haven't changed dramatically, but ongoing costs can be much lower if you choose the right architecture from the start. And the performance gap between cheap sites and premium ones has widened — because the premium builders now have access to infrastructure that used to require enterprise budgets.</p>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The Real Cost Difference in 2026</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">A £3K website built on Cloudflare with Astro will outperform a £15K WordPress site in speed, SEO, and total cost of ownership. The build cost is similar — the ongoing cost (hosting, plugins, security patches, performance optimisation) is where you save thousands per year.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Questions to Ask -->
        <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-indigo-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-indigo-400 pl-4">Questions to Ask Before Signing</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">Before committing to any web developer or agency, ask these questions. The answers will tell you more about their competence than their portfolio ever could:</p>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 space-y-3">
          <div class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-700/50 bg-gray-900/20">
            <p class="text-sm text-white font-medium">1. "What's my monthly cost after launch?"</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">If they can't give a clear answer, they haven't thought about it — or they're hiding it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-700/50 bg-gray-900/20">
            <p class="text-sm text-white font-medium">2. "Who owns the code and domain?"</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">You should own everything. If they retain code ownership or control your domain, walk away.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-700/50 bg-gray-900/20">
            <p class="text-sm text-white font-medium">3. "Can I move to another developer without rebuilding?"</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">Proprietary platforms and page builders create lock-in. Standard code (HTML, CSS, JS) is portable.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-700/50 bg-gray-900/20">
            <p class="text-sm text-white font-medium">4. "What happens if I need changes in 6 months?"</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">Understand the support model. Retainer? Pay-per-hour? Included in a maintenance package?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-700/50 bg-gray-900/20">
            <p class="text-sm text-white font-medium">5. "What's your approach to page speed and SEO?"</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">If they don't mention Core Web Vitals, structured data, or mobile performance unprompted — they're not thinking about it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-700/50 bg-gray-900/20">
            <p class="text-sm text-white font-medium">6. "Can I see a staging version before you launch?"</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">Any serious developer uses staging environments. If they push straight to live, that's a red flag.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-700/50 bg-gray-900/20">
            <p class="text-sm text-white font-medium">7. "What's included in your quote that other agencies charge extra for?"</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">This reveals what they consider standard vs premium. Compare like-for-like across providers.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-700/50 bg-gray-900/20">
            <p class="text-sm text-white font-medium">8. "How do you handle scope creep?"</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">Projects always evolve. Good developers have a transparent change request process with clear pricing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Summary -->
        <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-indigo-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-indigo-400 pl-4">Summary: What You'll Pay in 2026</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">Website pricing in the UK comes down to three things: what you need, how custom it is, and who builds it.</p>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-emerald-500/30 bg-emerald-950/10">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">✅ Key Takeaways</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 space-y-2">
            <li>• Budget £1-3K for a simple brochure site, £3-10K for a proper business site, £10K+ for anything with complex functionality</li>
            <li>• Ongoing costs (£100-500/month) are often larger than the initial build over a 3-year period</li>
            <li>• Modern edge-deployed sites can reduce hosting costs to near-zero while improving performance</li>
            <li>• The cheapest quote rarely delivers the best value — factor in rebuild costs, downtime, and missed SEO opportunities</li>
            <li>• Always get a detailed scope document before signing anything</li>
            <li>• Ask about ownership, portability, and post-launch support before choosing a developer</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">Here's the final reference table:</p>

